<p />
<h1><a name="Email_Reports_Perl_Infrastructur"></a> Email Reports: Perl Infrastructure Developer Notes. </h1>
<p />
<p />
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Introduction_to_perl_based_repor"></a> Introduction to perl-based reports. </span></h2>
<p />
There is a perl-based email report structure independent of the python system that interfaces with OIM / MyOSG in order to produce tailored reports for those site and VO admins who might have requested same.
<p />
The reports are:
<p /> <ul>
<li> OSG VO metrics, sent weekly, monthly and yearly to people registered in OIM to receive such reports; and
</li> <li> OSG site metrics sent weekly and monthly to site admins registered to receive such reports in OIM. These are aggregated per person <em>ie</em> a site admin registered to receive reports for three sites will receive a single report given separate and total usage information about all three sites.
</li></ul> 
<p />
In the SourceForge repository, these reports are <code>gratia/reporting/summary/all-vos-oim</code> and <code>gratia/reporting/summary/all-sites-oim</code> respectively.
<p />
In addition, common code is stored in perl modules under <code>gratia/reporting/summary/GratiaReporting</code>.
<p />
